    <div class="presentation row">
        <div class="col-12 col-md-8">
            <div class="description"><p><span class="testo">On April 25, 1951, was published in Bologna the first issue of the&nbsp;<strong>review "il Mulino".</strong></span></p>
<p class="testo">In a short time, "il Mulino" became one of the most interesting reference points in Italy for the political and cultural debate, and established important editorial relationships in Italy and abroad.</p>
<p class="testo">Editorial activities evolved along with the review: in 1954 was founded the&nbsp;<strong>il Mulino publishing house&nbsp;</strong>(Societ&agrave; editrice il Mulino), and were initiated research projects (focusing mostly on the educational institutions and the political system in Italy), that eventually led, in 1964, to the establishment of the&nbsp;<strong>Istituto Carlo Cattaneo</strong>.</p>
<p class="testo">In 1964 all the activities were methodically restructured, and placed under the control of the&nbsp;<strong>Associazione di cultura e di politica "il Mulino"</strong>, a non-profit association of people who contributed to the development of the group's various activities.</p>
<p class="testo"><span>Il Mulino publishing house</span><br><span>Strada Maggiore 37 - 40125 Bologna</span><br><span>Tel 051 256011 - info@mulino.it</span><br><span>Partita iva:&nbsp;</span><span>00311580377</span></p></div>
        </div>
